# CODEOWNERS
#
# GitHub uses this file to auto-request reviews and (with branch protection)
# to REQUIRE an approving review from a code owner before a PR can merge into
# `main`. This operationalizes FR-3.1 ("at least one approved review from a
# qualified reviewer, not the author") and AC-7 for the Code Review & Merge
# Pipeline PRD.
#
# Syntax: <path-pattern> <@owner> [<@owner> ...]
# Later, more-specific rules win. Every merged PR that touches a matched path
# requires an approval from a listed owner.
#
# NOTE: the repo's own audit engine (api/src/application/tools/AuditRunner.ts)
# credits this file toward the CC1/CC3–CC5 change-management controls; its
# matcher accepts .github/CODEOWNERS, docs/CODEOWNERS, or a root CODEOWNERS.

# Default owner for everything not matched by a more specific rule below.
*                       @SeanHogg

# Backend / API and agent-runtime (highest scrutiny — core application code).
